snippet.textDisplay:
Okay, hear me out. I live in Norway above the Arctic circle. I can get a very limited range of chilis, all fresh. I can dry them myself of course, but are there any alternatives for the very South American varieties, when my international supermarkets are primarily Asian or Middle Eastern?
The ones I know I can get (from the recipe) are jalapeños. That's it. Maybe I can find whole Chipotles, but last time I had to buy Chipotle tabasco. I don't have a smoker.

snippet.textDisplay:
I've said before that Babish is the only gringo that seems to respect Mexican cuisine and cook it properly. This is so true, that this recipe, that it's supposed to be Tex-mex, not Mexican, was cooked by him and made it look like authentic Mexican cuisine.
This Carnivorous Chili is basically Asado Rojo, a super common dish in the North of Mexico, also called Asado de Bodas, as it is served in many weddings, Quinceañeras and parties in general. The main difference is that we do brown all the meat, repeat: we brown all the meat.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Andrew,
I just want to thank you because I’ve always loved cooking but your videos and awesome personality really kicked things off for me. I’m currently a college student and I’m my free time I’ve dedicated most of it to cooking. Your videos are amazing and a huge inspiration for me. I’ve struggled with anxiety most of my life and cooking has been the only thing that truly calms me down and makes me the happiest I can be. You always say your goal is to get people cooking, and I can say with true confidence that that is exactly what you do. Thanks from all of us and keep up the amazing videos.
Best,
Luke
snippet.textOriginal:
Hey Andrew,
I just want to thank you because I’ve always loved cooking but your videos and awesome personality really kicked things off for me. I’m currently a college student and I’m my free time I’ve dedicated most of it to cooking. Your videos are amazing and a huge inspiration for me. I’ve struggled with anxiety most of my life and cooking has been the only thing that truly calms me down and makes me the happiest I can be. You always say your goal is to get people cooking, and I can say with true confidence that that is exactly what you do. Thanks from all of us and keep up the amazing videos. 
Best,
Luke
